Humanistic Buddhism  is a modern philosophy that emphasizes the importance of integrating Buddhist teachings with everyday life, promoting compassion, mindfulness, and social engagement. It seeks to make Buddhism more accessible and relevant to contemporary society by focusing on personal development, ethical behavior, and social responsibility. Humanistic Buddhism encourages individuals to cultivate inner peace and wisdom while also actively contributing to the well-being of others and the world around them.
