Monk, Householder, and Tantric Priest: Newar Buddhism Newar Buddhism embodies a diverse spectrum of spiritual paths, catering to the varied needs and inclinations of individuals within the community. The roles of monk, householder, and tantric priest showcase the multifaceted nature of Buddhist practice, offering pathways for those seeking solitude and renunciation, as well as for those engaging with the world in a more integrated manner. Each role carries its own unique set of responsibilities and practices, contributing to the rich tapestry of Newar Buddhist traditions.
